The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 August is 273,314 (485.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 August, there were 6,121 new confirmed cases (10.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 August, there were 5,137 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 19% (984 extra cases).
